<Collection><ShortName>HIR3SCOL</ShortName><VersionId>007</VersionId><InsertTime>2013-05-01T00:00:00.000Z</InsertTime><LastUpdate>2015-06-05T00:00:00.000Z</LastUpdate><LongName>HIRDLS/Aura Level 3 daily gridded 1 x 1 deg. stratospheric columns of NO2</LongName><DataSetId>HIRDLS/Aura Level 3 daily gridded 1 x 1 deg. stratospheric columns of NO2 V007</DataSetId><Description>HIR3SCOL is the EOS High Resolution Dynamics Limb Sounder (HIRDLS/Aura) level 3 daily gridded 1 x 1 deg. stratospheric columns of NO2 (nitrogen dioxide) data product. The current version is 7. The product contains 1 x 1 degree gridded data between +80 to -64 degrees latitude. The stratospheric column is computed from data at 57 to 1.0 hPa. The product consists of one file spanning the entire HIRDLS mission from January 22, 2005 through March 17, 2008. Users of the HIR3SCOL data product should read the Version 7 HIRDLS Data Description and Quality document for more information

The data are stored in the version 5 EOS Hierarchical Data Format (HDF-EOS5), which is based on the version 5 Hierarchical Data Format, or HDF5. The data file contains one grid object with data fields, attributes, and metadata. The data fields include the stratospheric column amount, precision (standard deviation), and data counts per grid cell. Time, latitude and longitude information are also included in the file.

Parameters contained in the data files include the following:
Variable Name|Description|Units
NO2|Nitrogen Dioxide (NO2) Volume Mixing Ratio|mol/mol
End of parameter information</Description><Orderable>false</Orderable><Visible>true</Visible><RevisionDate>2015-06-05T00:00:00.000Z</RevisionDate><ArchiveCenter>GESDISC</ArchiveCenter><CitationForExternalPublication>
